## Epic execution

An explicit `implement the PRD` request freezes the accepted target and creates one visible task and one deterministic Execution Run per independently shippable Epic. Dependency-ready Epics may start together. Each Epic gets one integration branch and one Project PR.

The visible task receives a compact launch envelope. Bootstrap verifies the immutable source and loads the complete relevant Epic once. Child Tickets receive only their accepted source slices, dependency contracts, and proof expectations; they never receive the complete PRD, run history, or unrelated receipts.

The parent owns user decisions, shared contracts, integration, the acceptance oracle, final verification, pull requests, merge, release, rollback, and canonical-document updates. Delegate only work with independent ownership and proof. Disk run state is authoritative after launch; resume from the locked source, manifest, and compact resume artifact.

Run focused changed-behavior checks and one final Epic verification on the exact integrated revision. Consequence-specific specialists run only when the accepted Epic declares the relevant trigger. Review findings cannot expand the accepted product and must end as `fixed`, `ask user`, `deferred`, or `omitted`.

Implementation stops for a material unresolved product decision, missing authority, unsafe or destructive behavior absent from the accepted document, preservation risk, or required proof that cannot be obtained. Follow `$GAUNTLET_ROOT/docs/prd-execution.md` for controller commands and release mechanics.
